==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Holmium
<hw>Hol"mi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Stock<ets>holm</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A rare element of
atomic number 67 said to be contained in gadolinite. Chemical symbol Ho.
Atomic weight 164.93. Valence +3. It was detected by spectral absorption
bands in 1878 by the <persfn>Delafontaine</persfn> and
<persfn>Soret</persfn>, who called it "Element X". Later the Swedish
chemist <persfn>Cleve</persfn> independently discovered it in erbia, and
named it after his native city Stockholm. The first preparation of pure
Holmia, the yellow oxide, was not made until 1911.</def> <au>HCP61</au>
-- <wordforms><wf>Hol"mic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Holmos</ent>⟦br⟧
